        <h2> How to use:</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
            <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-caret-square-o-down"></i>
              First set the colors of each team by typing in their color. The color entry accepts almost any color you can think of (you can also enter hex colors)! Timer colors will then match the team colors.</p>
              <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-clock-o"></i> Each timer corresponds to a seat. When the skater’s butt hits the seat, tap or click the corresponding timer, and it will start their 30 second countdown. If you need to pause an individual timer for any reason, tapping it a second time will pause it.</p>
              <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-exclamation-circle"></i> You will get a warning when there are 13 seconds remaining on their clock, at which point you can begin the give the command to stand (“Color, number, stand”). You should be saying “stand” as the timer hits 10. If they fail to stand at 10 seconds, you can tap or click their timer to pause the countdown until they stand. Tap it again once they’re standing, and the countdown resumes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
              <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-exclamation-circle"></i> You will get another warning when the clock hits 3 seconds remaining, at which point you can begin the give the command to leave the box (“Color, number, done”). You should be saying “done” as the timer hits zero.</p>
              <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-repeat"></i> Jammer timers have the same functionality, plus extra. If you have one jammer in the box, and the second jammer comes in, tapping their timer will result in the first jammer being released, and the second jammer’s timer will automatically populate with the amount of time that the first jammer served.</p>
              <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-pause"></i> If the jam is called off with skater(s) in the box, the large “JAM STOP” button will pause all timers currently running. When the next jam begins, the same button (that now says “JAM START”), will restart all timers that were running.</p>
              <!-- <p><i class="fa fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-repeat"></i> At halftime, when the team switches sides, click the “Halftime Swap” button, and team colors and any carryover penalties will switch sides. </p> -->
            </div>
